Use the standard library
This is how to mean_absolute_deviation of numbers:
   Remember that n is numbers's length
   Remember that total is tofloat of 0
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this n times:
      Remember that total is sum of total and item i in numbers
      Increase i
   End do
   Remember that mean is quotient of total and (tofloat of n)
   Remember that dev_total is tofloat of 0
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this n times:
      Remember that d is abs of (diff of item i in numbers and mean)
      Remember that dev_total is sum of dev_total and d
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is quotient of dev_total and (tofloat of n)
Now you know
>>> mean_absolute_deviation of [1.000000, 2.000000, 3.000000, 4.000000] 
1.000000
>>> mean_absolute_deviation of [1.000000, 2.000000, 3.000000] 
0.666667
>>> mean_absolute_deviation of [1.000000, 2.000000, 3.000000, 4.000000] 
1.000000